ur%20career.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKevin%20Legg%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Sage%2C%20a%20company%20developing%20training%20and%20curriculums%20for%20workplaces%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F08%2F16%2F3-unexpected-traits-of-bad-bosses-and-tell-tale-signs-of-dysfunction.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20CNBC%20in%20an%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20one%20of%20the%20most%20unexpected%20traits%20of%20a%20poor%20manager%20is%20actually%20%26quot%3Bundermanaging%26quot%3B%20employees.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20undermanaging%20boss%20falters%20at%20the%20prospect%20of%20making%20difficult%20decisions%20and%20%26quot%3Bwill%20experience%20decision%20paralysis%2C%20making%20a%20bad%20situation%20even%20worse%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Legg.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegg%20explained%20that%20undermanagers%20mask%20their%20toxicity%20through%20empty%20goodwill%20gestures.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20make%20matters%20worse%2C%20bad%20bosses%20are%20continually%20making%20a%20virtue%20out%20of%20undermanagement%20%E2%80%A6%20%5Bby%20saying%2C%20for%20example%5D%20'My%20people%20can%20come%20to%20me%20if%20they%20need%20me%20%E2%80%93%20my%20door%20is%20open%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegg%20says%20that%20this%20type%20of%20manager%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Blazy%20boss%20who%20lacks%20the%20courage%20or%20work%20ethic%20to%20really%20coach%20and%20lead.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20will%20negatively%20impact%20direct%20reports%2C%20especially%20junior%20staffers%20who%20will%20have%20to%20learn%20to%20manage%20themselves.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20medium%20term%2C%20there%20is%20resentment%20at%20annual%20reviews%20when%20folks%20are%20passed%20over%20for%20promotions%20because%20they%20never%20lived%20up%20to%20a%20standard%20they%20were%20never%20shown%2C%26quot%3B%20Legg%20said%20saying%20those%20employees%20eventually%20leave%20for%20managers%20that