20in%20past%20court%20judgments%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThese%20words%20are%20improper%20and%20have%20been%20used%20for%20women%20in%20court%20judgments.%20This%20handbook's%20objective%20is%20not%20to%20criticise%20those%20judgments%20or%20doubt%20them.%20This%20is%20just%20to%20underline%20how%20gender%20stereotypes%20are%20perpetuated%20inadvertently.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20how%20stereotypes%20may%20impact%20judicial%20decision-making%2C%20the%20handbook%20states%2C%20%26quot%3BLike%20any%20person%2C%20a%20judge%20may%20also%20unconsciously%20hold%20or%20rely%20on%20stereotypes.%20If%20a%20judge%20relies%20on%20preconceived%20assumptions%20about%20people%20or%20groups%20when%20deciding%20cases%20or%20writing%20judgements%2C%20the%20harm%20caused%20can%20be%20enormous.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20when%20judges%20reach%20legally%20correct%20outcomes%2C%20the%20use%20of%20reasoning%20or%20language%20that%20promotes%20gender%20stereotypes%20undermines%20the%20unique%20characteristics%2C%20autonomy%2C%20and%20dignity%20of%20the%20individuals%20before%20the%20court%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20stated%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20use%20of%20stereotypes%20by%20judges%20also%20has%20the%20effect%20of%20entrenching%20and%20perpetuating%20stereotypes%2C%20creating%20a%20vicious%20cycle%20of%20injustice.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EListing%20several%20stereotypical%20words%20and%20their%20alternatives%2C%20the%20handbook%20stated%20that%20words%20such%20as%20%26quot%3Bfaggot%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bfallen%20woman%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bharlot%26quot%3B%20need%20to%20be%20done%20away%20with%20in%20court%20judgments.%20Instead%2C%20it%20said%2C%20judges%20should%20accurately%20describe%20the%20sexual%20orientation%20of%20the%20person%20concerned%20--%20homosexual%20or%20bisexual%2C%20use%20%26quot%3Bwoman%26quot%3B%20and%20avoid%20words%20such%20as%20%26quot%3Bfallen%20woman%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bharlot%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%220hvleboo%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2F0hvleboo_supreme-court_625x300_16_August_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESource%3A%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20website%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELikewise%2C%20words%20such%20as%20%26quot%3Bdutiful%20wife%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bobedient%20wife%26quot%3B%20should%20be%20avoided%2C%20the%20handbook%20stated.%20The%20use%20of%20words%20such%20as%20%26quot%3Bravished%26quot%3B%20in%20cases%20of%20sexual%20assault%20or%20rape%20was%20also%20red-flagged%20in%20the%20handbook.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20handbook%20also%20busted%20several%20stereotypes%20attached%20to%20women%2C%20such%20as%20women%20being%20overly%20emotional%20and%20indecisive%2C%20unmarried%20women%20being%20incapable%20of%20taking%20decisions%20and%20all%20women%20wanting%20to%20have%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20glossary%20aims%20to%20help%20the%20Indian%20judiciary%20identify%20and%20mitigate%20the%20use%20of%20stereotypes%20and%20stereotype-enforcing%20language%20against%20women%20in%20their%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20states%20the%20handbook%2C%20which%20has%20now%20been%20uploaded%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692178020000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2F4qgfvaco_supreme-court-new_625x300_11_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-chief-justice-of-india-dy-chandrachud-no-concubine-ladylike-dutiful-wife-supreme-courts-new-handbook-4302063%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Prostitute%2C%20hooker%2C%20whore%2C%20keep%2C%20mistress%2C%20slut%20--%20these%20are%20among%2040-odd%20words%20red-flagged%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20its%20latest%20handbook%20to%20sensitise%20judges%20against%20inadvertently%20furthering%20gender%20biases%20by%20using%20stereotypical%20words%20in%20court%20judgments%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-chief-justice-of-india-dy-chandrachud-no-concubine-ladylike-dutiful-wife-supreme-courts-new-handbook-4302063%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-chief-justice-of-india-dy-chandrachud-no-concubine-ladylike-dutiful-wife-supreme-courts-new-handbook-4302063%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-chief-justice-of-india-dy-chandrachud-no-concubine-ladylike-dutiful-wife-supreme-courts-new-handbook-4302063%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22TikTok%20influencers%20want%20to%20rent%20you%20a%20very%20cool%20home.%20Just%20don't%20call%20them%20landlords.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20house%20has%20multiple%20individuals%20in%20rooms%20swiped%20in%20and%20out%2C%20much%20like%20a%20person%20scrolling%20through%20TikTok%20videos%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64dbd9d84ef9f30019f78d46%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESocial%20media%20sparked%20a%20rise%20in%20the%20popularity%20of%20%26quot%3Bhouse%20hacking%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20fancy%20new%20term%20for%20the%20age-old%20concept%20of%20being%20a%20landlord%20that%20has%20been%20repackaged%20for%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20real-estate%20investors.%3Cp%3EArantza%20Pena%20Popo%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELate%20last%20year%2C%20Kelly%20Clark%20was%20flush%20with%20cash%20from%20a%20divorce%20settlement%20and%20eager%20to%20embark%20on%20a%20new%20career.%20It%20was%20finally%20time%2C%20she%20decided%2C%20to%20become%20a%20landlord.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClark%2C%20who%20worked%20in%20computer%20sales%20and%20interior%20design%20before%20leaving%20the%20workforce%20to%20raise%20her%20children%2C%20had%20come%20across%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bhouse%20hacking%26quot%3B%20while%20scrolling%20through%20BiggerPockets%2C%20a%20real-estate-investing%20website.%20In%20forums%20and%20webinars%2C%20investors%20sang%20the%20praises%20of%20buying%20up%20a%20house%20or%20small%20multiunit%20building%2C%20living%20in%20part%20of%20the%20home%2C%20and%20renting%20out%20the%20rest%20to%20tenants%20who%20cover%20the%20mortgage%20payments%20each%20month.%20Her%20then-husband%20scoffed%20at%20the%20notion%20of%20taking%20on%20roommates%20and%20sacrificing%20their%20hard-earned%20privacy.%20Despite%20his%20protests%2C%20Clark%20found%20the%20idea%20tantalizing.%20After%20all%2C%20who%20wouldn't%20want%20to%20live%20pretty%20much%20for%20free%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20age%20of%2056%2C%20Clark%20got%20her%20chance.%20In%20January%2C%20she%20bought%20a%20modest%20four-unit%20apartment%20building%20in%20Spokane%2C%20Washington%2C%20for%20%24399%2C000.%20With%20a%20loan%20insured%20by%20the%20Federal%20Housing%20Administration%2C%20she%20put%20down%20just%203.5%25%20of%20that%20sticker%20price%2C%20or%20roughly%20%2414%2C000%2C%20and%20poured%20another%20%24100%2C000%20of%20her%20savings%20into%20renovating%20the%20century-old%20property.%20She%20lives%20in%20one%20of%20the%20units%20and%20plans%20to%20rent%20out%20the%20other%20three%20at%20prices%20that%20will%20more%20than%20cover%20her%20%242%2C800%20monthly%20mortgage%20payment.%20The%20terms%20of%20her%20loan%20require%20that%20she%20live%20at%20the%20property%20for%20at%20least%20a%20year%2C%20but%20Clark%20said%20she%20hoped%20to%20eventually%20refinance%20the%20property%20and%20apply%20the%20same%20strategy%20to%20additional%20investments.%20Recently%2C%20she%20got%20a%20letter%20from%20her%20insurance%20company%20informing%20her%20that%20the%20building%20was%20valued%20at%20more%20than%20%24800%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20love%20to%20spend%20my%20entire%20life%20house%20hacking%2C%26quot%3B%20Clark%2C%20who%20now%20helps%20other%20investors%20find%20and%20manage%20properties%2C%20told%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20live-in%20landlords%20are%20far%20from%20a%20novel%20concept%2C%20the%20pandemic-era%20fever%20around%20passive%20income%20and%20real-estate%20investing%20has%20sparked%20a%20rise%20in%20the%20popularity%20of%20house%20hacking.%20TikTok%20influencers%20and%20real-estate%20gurus%20quickly%20picked%20up%20on%20this%20fervor.%20Using%20flashy%2C%20emoji-laden%20graphics%20and%20buzzwords%20like%20%26quot%3Bliving%20for%20free%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bthe%20simplest%20way%20to%20become%20a%20millionaire%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20brandish%20house%20hacking%20as%20a%20no-brainer%20for%20those%20looking%20to%20make%20money%20in%20real%20estate%20and%20get%20their%20foot%20in%20the%20door%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-ice-age-higher-home-prices-fewer-sales-inventory-2023-5%5C%22%3Etoday's%20brutal%20housing%20market%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20approach%20isn't%20limited%20to%20those%20with%20rich%20parents%20or%20lucrative%20jobs%3A%20With%20the%20aid%20of%20government-backed%20loans%20that%20require%20smaller%20down%20payments%2C%20they%20say%2C%20pretty%20much%20anyone%20can%20hack%20their%20way%20to%20wealth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20more%20complicated%20than%20that.%20Hackers%20take%20on%20large%20amounts%20of%20debt%20to%20fund%20their%20purchases%2C%20which%20could%20pose%20a%20risk%20if%20home%20prices%20fall.%20Aside%20from%20typical%20roommate%20issues%20%E2%80%94%20clean%20the%20dishes%20in%20the%20sink%2C%20anyone%3F%20%E2%80%94%20house%20hackers%20need%20to%20brace%20themselves%20for%20the%20possibility%20that%20they'll%20have%20trouble%20finding%20tenants%2C%20or%20end%20up%20with%20renters%20who%20damage%20the%20property%20or%20don't%20pay%20on%20time.%20And%20then%20there's%20the%20backlash%20against%20the%20very%20idea%3A%20Online%20commenters%20have%20accused%20house%20hackers%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-investing-house-hackers-anti-landlord-tiktok-2022-4%5C%22%3Eexploiting%20their%20tenants%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESilicon%20Valley%20%26quot%3Btrailblazers%26quot%3B%20are%20fond%20of%20rediscovering%20businesses%20that%20already%20exist%20%E2%80%94%20from%20buses%20and%20offices%20to%20dorms%20and%20juices%20%E2%80%94%20and%20selling%20them%20at%20a%20fat%20markup.%20In%20that%20sense%2C%20the%20use%20of%20house%20hacking%20can%20be%20viewed%20as%20just%20a%20thinly%20veiled%20attempt%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcommentisfree%2F2023%2Ffeb%2F21%2Flandlords-are-rebranded-as-house-hackers-and-capitalism-is-sanitised-once-again%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erebrand%20and%20sanitize%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Blandlord%2C%26quot%3B%20conjuring%20images%20of%20tech-enabled%20progress%2C%20rather%20than%20the%20balding%20guy%20down%20the%20hall%20who%20picks%20up%20your%20rent%20check%20each%20month.%20The%20great%20innovation%20of%20house%20hacking%20is%20just%20a%20flashy%20repackaging%20of%20an%20age-old%20idea%20for%20a%20new%20crop%20of%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20namely%2C%20millennials%20and%20Gen%20Zers.%20But%20even%20if%20the%20methods%20aren't%20exactly%20original%2C%20the%20broad%20adoption%20of%20the%20terminology%20shows%20how%20pretty%20much%20everyone%20is%20searching%20for%20an%20edge%20in%20today's%20cutthroat%20housing%20market%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Hack'%20your%20way%20to%20wealth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBrandon%20Turner%2C%20an%20influential%20figurehead%20of%20BiggerPockets%2C%20kicked%20off%20the%20house-hacking%20craze%20in%202013%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fool.com%2Finvesting%2Fgeneral%2F2013%2F12%2F21%2Fhow-to-hack-your-housing-and-get-paid-to-live-for.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblog%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%20titled%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20to%20'hack'%20your%20housing%20and%20get%20paid%20to%20live%20for%20free.%26quot%3B%20The%20post%20outlined%20a%20simple%20way%20for%20anyone%20%E2%80%94%20well%2C%20at%20least%20those%20with%20%26quot%3Bdecent%20credit%2C%20a%20stable%20job%2C%20and%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20savings%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20to%20free%20themselves%20from%20the%20shackles%20of%20renting%20and%20start%20building%20wealth%20through%20real%20estate.%20The%20key%2C%20Turner%20wrote%2C%20was%20to%20purchase%20a%20small%20multifamily%20property%20such%20as%20a%20duplex%2C%20triplex%2C%20or%20four-plex%2C%20live%20in%20one%20of%20the%20units%2C%20and%20rent%20out%20the%20others%20for%20more%20than%20the%20monthly%20mortgage%20payment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20much%20more%20than%20simple%20tricks%20or%20ideas%20to%20shave%20five%20minutes%20off%20your%20workday%2C%26quot%3B%20Turner%2C%20who%20left%20the%20company%20last%20year%20to%20focus%20on%20his%20own%20investment%20firm%2C%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20epic%2C%20life-changing%20stuff.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20post%20became%20hugely%20influential%2C%20inspiring%20thousands%20of%20copycats%20who%20iterated%20on%20the%20idea.%20While%20Turner's%20initial%20strategy%20emphasized%20small%20multifamily%20buildings%2C%20some%20house%20hackers%20applied%20the%20concept%20to%20single-family%20homes.%20Ryan%20Lehman%2C%20a%2025-year-old%20software%20engineer%20and%20real-estate%20investor%20in%20Seattle%2C%20told%20me%20he%20got%20his%20start%20by%20reading%20books%2C%20talking%20to%20investors%2C%20and%2C%20of%20course%2C%20spending%20time%20on%20BiggerPockets.%20Lehman%20said%20he%20was%20drawn%20to%20Turner%2C%20who%20didn't%20grow%20up%20around%20the%20real-estate%20business%20and%20rose%20to%20fame%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-investing-guru-brandon-turner-biggerpockets-profile-2021-10%5C%22%3Etouting%20a%20simple%20approach%20to%20investing%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20focused%20on%20achieving%20financial%20freedom.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20'If%20Brandon%20can%20do%20this%2C%20I%20can%20probably%20do%20it%2C'%26quot%3B%20Lehman%20told%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20August%202020%2C%20Lehman%20arrived%20in%20Seattle%20and%20briefly%20rented%20a%20room%20from%20a%20couple%20of%20house%20hackers%20who%20offered%20to%20show%20him%20how%20they%20managed%20various%20aspects%20of%20being%20a%20landlord%2C%20including%20maintenance%20and%20rent%20collection.%20A%20few%20months%20later%2C%20he%20bought%20a%20five-bedroom%20home%20for%20%24620%2C000%2C%20putting%20down%205%25%20of%20the%20purchase%20price%20with%20savings%20from%20internships%20and%20earnings%20from%20the%20stock%20market.%20It%20was%20a%20challenge%20to%20find%20tenants%20at%20first%2C%20he%20said%2C%20but%20by%20sacrificing%20some%20privacy%2C%20he%20was%20able%20to%20cover%20his%20expenses%20each%20month%20%E2%80%94%20without%20pulling%20from%20his%20own%20pocket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20basically%20bought%20my%20house%2C%20and%20then%20everything%20started%20by%20kind%20of%20going%20crazy%20as%20far%20as%20house%20prices%20and%20stuff%20like%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Lehman%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20some%20skill%20I%20guess%2C%20just%20from%20learning%20and%20making%20sure%20I'm%20not%20doing%20anything%20crazy.%20But%20there's%20so%20much%20luck%20involved.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20key%20component%20of%20house%20hacking%20is%20the%20use%20of%20low-down-payment%20loans%20from%20the%20Federal%20Housing%20Administration.%20Unlike%20loans%20for%20investment%20properties%2C%20which%20typically%20require%20the%20buyer%20to%20put%20down%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lendingtree.com%2Fhome%2Fmortgage%2Fdown-payment-for-rental-property%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eat%20least%2015%25%20of%20the%20purchase%20price%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20these%20loans%20offer%20buyers%20with%20lower%20credit%20scores%20or%20income%20the%20opportunity%20to%20put%20down%20as%20little%20as%203.5%25.%20The%20catch%20with%20these%20loans%20is%20that%20you%20need%20to%20stay%20at%20the%20property%20for%20at%20least%20a%20year.%20But%20even%20that%20isn't%20much%20of%20an%20obstacle%20for%20those%20looking%20to%20build%20a%20miniempire%20of%20real%20estate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EThere's%20some%20skill%20I%20guess%2C%20just%20from%20learning%20and%20making%20sure%20I'm%20not%20doing%20anything%20crazy.%20But%20there's%20so%20much%20luck%20involved.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20buying%20his%20first%20house%20at%2024%2C%20Craig%20Curelop%2C%20a%20former%20employee%20of%20BiggerPockets%20who's%20now%20a%20Realtor%20focused%20on%20helping%20investors%2C%20told%20me%20that%20he%20began%20moving%20into%20a%20new%20property%20every%2012%20months%20%26quot%3Blike%20clockwork%2C%26quot%3B%20taking%20on%20a%20new%20loan%20each%20time%20and%20refinancing%20other%20properties%20in%20his%20growing%20portfolio.%20In%202019%2C%20he%20published%20a%20book%20called%20%26quot%3BThe%20House%20Hacking%20Strategy%3A%20How%20to%20Use%20Your%20Home%20to%20Achieve%20Financial%20Freedom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20mortgage%20payments%20high%20and%20rent%20so%20high%20and%20all%20of%20that%2C%20how%20do%20you%20get%20ahead%20in%20this%20world%20where%20wages%20aren't%20rising%20but%20costs%20are%3F%26quot%3B%20Curelop%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20all%20of%20this%20'Woe%20is%20me'%20talk%2C%20but%20then%20there's%20a%20handful%20of%20people%20that%20are%20actually%20doing%20something%20about%20it.%20And%20I%20think%20house%20hacking%20is%20one%20obvious%20way%20to%20eliminate%2C%20or%20at%20least%20drastically%20reduce%2C%20what%20likely%20is%20your%20largest%20expense.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESelling%20the%20dream%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou'd%20be%20forgiven%20for%20thinking%20that%20all%20this%20sounds%20sort%20of%20ho-hum%20%E2%80%94%20a%20mere%20refresh%20of%20the%20ancient%20idea%20of%20owning%20and%20renting%20out%20property.%20In%20fact%2C%20a%20huge%20swath%20of%20landlords%20in%20the%20US%20could%20fall%20under%20the%20%26quot%3Bhouse%20hacker%26quot%3B%20umbrella%3A%20Of%20the%20roughly%2049.5%20million%20rental%20units%20in%20the%20US%2C%20about%2046%25%20are%20on%20small%20rental%20properties%20with%20between%20one%20and%20four%20units%2C%20according%20to%20the%20US%20Census%20Bureau.%20About%2070%25%20of%20those%20small%20rental%20properties%2C%20or%20about%2015.9%20million%2C%20are%20owned%20by%20individual%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20online%20influencers%20have%20worked%20hard%20to%20make%20the%20idea%20seem%20groundbreaking%20and%20alluring%20to%20young%20investors%20and%20people%20who%20are%20sick%20of%20their%209-to-5%20jobs.%20TikTok%20is%20full%20of%20videos%20that%20break%20down%20the%20strategy%2C%20often%20in%20effusive%20terms%20that%20sell%20the%20idea%20of%20%26quot%3Bliving%20for%20free%26quot%3B%20or%20never%20having%20to%20pay%20rent%20again.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWait%2C%20you're%20my%20landlord%3F%26quot%3B%20the%20personal-finance%20influencer%20Addison%20Jarman%2C%20playing%20the%20role%20of%20an%20astonished%20renter%2C%20asks%20in%20one%20TikTok%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYeah%2C%20it's%20called%20'house%20hacking%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20owner%20and%20roommate%2C%20also%20played%20by%20Jarman%2C%20who%20has%204%20million%20followers%2C%20replies.%20%26quot%3BI%20make%20%241%2C900%20off%20y'all%20paying%20rent%20each%20month.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EYouTube%20will%20definitely%20make%20it%20seem%20very%20easy%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20some%20property%20owners%20and%20real-estate%20influencers%20have%20even%20insisted%20upon%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.curbed.com%2F2022%2F06%2Flandlords-housing-providers-semantics.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edoing%20away%20with%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Blandlord%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20altogether%20and%20replacing%20it%20with%20euphemisms%20like%20%26quot%3Bhousing%20provider.%26quot%3B%20The%20term%20%26quot%3Bhouse%20hacker%26quot%3B%20offers%20a%20similar%20shield%3A%20If%20you%20own%20a%20house%20and%20are%20renting%20out%20a%20couple%20of%20rooms%20to%20friends%20who%20cover%20your%20mortgage%2C%20it%20may%20sound%20kinder%20than%20calling%20yourself%20their%20landlord.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20term%20'landlord'%20is%20archaic%2C%20offensive%2C%20and%20divisive%2C%26quot%3B%20Jay%20Parsons%2C%20the%20head%20of%20economics%20for%20RealPage%2C%20a%20real-estate-software%20company%2C%20tweeted%20in%20November%202021.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20it's%20used%20more%20by%20reporters%2Fpolicymakers%20than%20it%20is%20used%20in%20real%20life%20everywhere%20but%20in%20a%20few%20big%20coastal%20cities%20like%20NYC%20and%20SF.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Liang%2C%20a%20YouTuber%20and%20TikToker%20who%20shares%20tips%20on%20credit%20cards%2C%20personal%20finance%2C%20and%20real%20estate%20to%20an%20audience%20of%20more%20than%202.3%20million%20TikTok%20followers%2C%20said%20house%20hacking%20represented%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20more%20accessible%20ways%26quot%3B%20for%20people%20to%20jump%20into%20the%20housing%20market.%20The%20ability%20to%20finance%20nearly%2097%25%20of%20the%20purchase%20opens%20the%20door%20to%20buyers%20who%20don't%20have%20huge%20piles%20of%20savings%2C%20he%20said.%20And%20the%20strategy%20solves%20several%20problems%20at%20once%3A%20the%20questions%20of%20where%20you'll%20lay%20your%20head%20at%20night%2C%20how%20you'll%20pay%20for%20it%2C%20and%20how%20you'll%20build%20wealth.%20In%20May%2C%20Liang%20posted%20a%20TikTok%20video%20in%20which%20he%20acted%20out%20a%20scenario%20between%20a%20house%20hacker%20and%20a%20pair%20of%20tenants%20whose%20rent%20payments%20exceeded%20the%20monthly%20mortgage%20expense.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWait%2C%20so%20we're%20buying%20you%20this%20house%3F%26quot%3B%20one%20renter%20asks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTechnically%2C%20you're%20paying%20me%20to%20buy%20this%20house%2C%26quot%3B%20Liang's%20landlord%20persona%20replies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20hacking%20haters%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20comments%20sections%20of%20several%20flashy%20TikTok%20posts%20on%20house%20hacking%2C%20some%20people%20pushed%20back%2C%20proposing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-investing-house-hackers-anti-landlord-tiktok-2022-4%5C%22%3Eharsher%20substitutes%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20term%2C%20including%20%26quot%3Bleech%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bparasite.%26quot%3B%20The%20complaints%20either%20revolved%20around%20the%20duplicity%20of%20posing%20as%20a%20roommate%20when%20you're%20really%20the%20landlord%20or%20the%20very%20act%20of%20using%20someone%20else's%20monthly%20payments%20to%20cover%20the%20expenses%20of%20a%20property%20%E2%80%94%20again%2C%20not%20a%20new%20concept.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20day-to-day%20life%2C%20some%20house%20hackers%20seek%20to%20avoid%20sticky%20situations%20by%20concealing%20that%20they're%20the%20owner%20of%20the%20house%2C%20hiring%20property%20managers%20to%20handle%20things%20such%20as%20rent%20collections%2C%20cleaning%20and%20maintenance%2C%20and%2C%20in%20the%20worst-case%20scenario%2C%20evictions.%20The%20hacker%20might%20then%20pose%20as%20just%20another%20tenant%2C%20or%20an%20associate%20of%20the%20management%20company.%20Curelop%2C%20who%20told%20me%20he's%20aware%20of%20this%20practice%2C%20said%20he's%20%26quot%3Bvery%20against%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20lying%20in%20any%20capacity%20is%20just%20wrong%20and%20shouldn't%20be%20done%2C%26quot%3B%20Curelop%20said.%20%26quot%3BMy%20suggestion%20is%20always%20to%20not%20flaunt%20that%20you%20own%20the%20place.%20If%20a%20tenant%20asks%2C%20don't%20lie.%20But%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20tell%20them%20if%20they%20don't%20ask.%20It's%20not%20really%20an%20important%20detail.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20his%20part%2C%20Liang%2C%20who%20now%20owns%20three%20multifamily%20properties%2C%20said%20he%20had%20no%20problem%20with%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Blandlord.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BI%20understand%2C%20definitely%2C%20some%20of%20the%20resentment%20toward%20landlords%20over%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Liang%20said.%20Curelop%20called%20the%20online%20backlash%20%26quot%3Bunfortunate%2C%26quot%3B%20making%20the%20case%20that%20%26quot%3Banyone%20can%20do%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20house%20hacking%20is%20often%20more%20accessible%20than%20other%20forms%20of%20real-estate%20investing%2C%20the%20videos%20used%20to%20sell%20people%20on%20it%20tend%20to%20gloss%20over%20the%20very%20real%20risks%20of%20buying%20up%20property%20%E2%80%94%20risks%20that%20both%20Liang%20and%20Curelop%20made%20sure%20to%20point%20out%20when%20I%20spoke%20with%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYouTube%20will%20definitely%20make%20it%20seem%20very%20easy%2C%26quot%3B%20Liang%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurelop%20said%20he%20emphasized%20to%20clients%20the%20importance%20of%20tenant%20screening%20to%20make%20sure%20they%20ended%20up%20with%20renters%20who%20would%20be%20considerate%20and%20prompt%20on%20payments.%20House%20hackers%20should%20also%20be%20prepared%20to%20front%20the%20entire%20mortgage%20payment%20if%20their%20roommate%20arrangement%20doesn't%20work%20out%20the%20way%20they'd%20hoped%2C%20although%20Curelop%20told%20me%20hackers%20are%20usually%20able%20to%20offset%20at%20least%20some%20of%20their%20mortgage%20by%20collecting%20rents%2C%20even%20if%20they%20have%20to%20lower%20prices.%20Plus%2C%20there%20are%20macroeconomic%20factors%20to%20consider%3A%20Rising%20home%20prices%20have%20made%20it%20tougher%20to%20find%20good%20deals%2C%20while%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frent-decline-fall-apartment-housing-market-landlords-tenant-lease-construction-2023-3%5C%22%3Erental%20market%20has%20softened%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20its%20COVID-19-era%20peak.%20Even%20Turner%2C%20the%20original%20house-hacking%20evangelist%2C%20told%20Insider%20in%202021%20that%20the%20rental%20market%20had%20shifted%20from%20%26quot%3Bsomething%20you%20can%20do%20as%20a%20mediocre%20investor%20to%20something%20you%20need%20to%20be%20an%20expert%20at.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%202012%2C%20any%20property%20you%20bought%20would%20make%20money%20as%20a%20rental%2C%26quot%3B%20Turner%20told%20Insider's%20Daniel%20Geiger.%20%26quot%3BToday%20if%20you%20take%20a%20random%20property%2C%20it%20will%20lose%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20benefit%20with%20house%20hacking%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20a%20regular%20investment%20property%2C%20is%20that%20it%20doesn't%20have%20to%20turn%20a%20profit%20for%20it%20to%20be%20considered%20worthwhile.%20If%20you're%20able%20to%20defray%20your%20housing%20costs%20at%20all%2C%20you%20may%20chalk%20that%20up%20as%20a%20win.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20no%20matter%20the%20semantics%2C%20house%20hackers%20can't%20fully%20insulate%20themselves%20from%20the%20sometimes%20messy%20realities%20of%20being%20a%20landlord.%20When%20I%20first%20spoke%20with%20Clark%2C%20the%20house%20hacker%20in%20Spokane%2C%20she%20was%20renovating%20one%20of%20her%20units%20and%20had%20another%20that'd%20been%20sitting%20on%20the%20market%20for%20three%20weeks%20%E2%80%94%20way%20longer%20than%20she'd%20wanted.%20She%20dropped%20the%20price%20and%20eventually%20found%20a%20tenant%2C%20but%20acknowledged%20that%20the%20rental%20market%20has%20cooled%20off%20from%20its%20heyday%20in%20spring%202022.%20Regardless%2C%20Clark%20told%20me%2C%20she'll%20be%20fine%20with%20the%20income%20she%20anticipates%20will%20one%20day%20materialize.%20And%20the%20temporary%20struggles%20haven't%20dimmed%20her%20view%20of%20house%20hacking.%