rticle%2Findia%2Fkrishna-janmabhoomi-trust-supreme-court-premises-survey-8893216%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%20Indian%20Express.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Trust%20in%20its%20petition%20has%20claimed%20that%20the%20Idgah%20mosque%20authorities%20have%20been%20using%20the%20premises%20as%20restrooms%20and%20for%20other%20necessities%20and%20that%20they%20are%20%E2%80%9Ccontinuously%20digging%20and%20destroying%20Hindu%20symbols%2C%20temple%20pillars%2C%20and%20other%20significant%20elements%20of%20the%20temple.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20had%20dismissed%20its%20application%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Cscientific%20survey%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20premises%2C%20where%20it%20believes%20the%20mosque%20had%20been%20constructed%20after%20the%20destruction%20of%20a%20temple.%20The%20high%20court%20was%20upholding%20a%20trial%20court%E2%80%99s%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Places%20of%20Worship%20(Special%20Provisions)%20Act%2C%201991%2C%20says%20that%20a%20mosque%2C%20temple%2C%20church%20or%20any%20place%20of%20public%20worship%20in%20existence%20on%20August%2015%201947%2C%20will%20retain%20the%20same%20religious%20character%20that%20it%20had%20on%20that%20day%20%E2%80%93%20irrespective%20of%20its%20history%20%E2%80%93%20and%20cannot%20be%20changed%20by%20the%20courts%20or%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692165643000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F18150906%2FSupreme-Court.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fshri-krishna-janmabhoomi-mathura-shahi-idgah-mosque-temple-supreme-court%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Shri%20Krishna%20Janmabhoomi%20Mukti%20Nirman%20Trust%20is%20appealing%20against%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court's%20stay%20on%20this%20plea.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fshri-krishna-janmabhoomi-mathura-shahi-idgah-mosque-temple-sup