%98India%20Ideas%20Summit%202020%E2%80%99%20that%20%E2%80%9CFDI%20inflows%20in%202019-20%20were%20%2474%20billion%2C%20a%20fifth%20more%20than%20the%20previous%20year.%20It%20was%20noteworthy%20that%20even%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20%2420%20billion%20of%20foreign%20investment%20flowed%20into%20India%20between%20April%20and%20July%20this%20year.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20illustrate%20that%20point%2C%20he%20said%20there%20are%20half%20a%20billion%20internet%20users%20in%20India%2C%20and%20the%20number%20in%20rural%20areas%20exceeds%20that%20in%20urban%20areas.%20Another%20half%20a%20billion%20are%20in%20the%20process%20of%20being%20connected%20and%20the%20food%20processing%20sector%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20worth%20half%20a%20trillion%20dollars%20by%202025%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20picture%20is%2C%20however%2C%20a%20little%20skewed%20as%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fprecipitous-decline-fdi-last-two-years-modi-tenure%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20July%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20chief%20economic%20advisor%20to%20the%20Modi%20government%2C%20Arvind%20Subramanian%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fprecipitous-decline-fdi-last-two-years-modi-tenure%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20his%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20India%20has%20not%20been%20able%20to%20raise%20FDI%20inflows%20from%20the%20low%20annual%20average%20of%202%25%20of%20GDP.%20In%20fact%2C%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20it%20has%20gone%20further%20down%20to%201.5%25%20of%20GDP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CForeign%20investment%20inflows%20(FDI)%20into%20India%20may%20be%20drying%20up%20even%20faster%20in%202023-24%20than%20in%202022-23%2C%20when%20net%20FDI%20inflows%20declined%2027%25%20to%20a%20mere%20%2428%20billion.%20It%20was%20the%20biggest%20decline%20in%20a%20decade.%20Many%20global%20analysts%20have%20expressed%20concern%20over%20the%20unprecedented%20decline%20in%20net%20FDI%20inflows%20in%202022-23.%20Now%2C%20it%20seems%20that%202023-24%20could%20be%20a%20bigger%20cause%20for%20worry.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20large%20part%20of%20the%20%2420%20billion%20FDI%20inflow%20that%20the%20prime%20minister%20spoke%20of%20was%20on%20account%20of%20what%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fmeghabahree%2F2020%2F07%2F15%2Fgoogle-joins-facebook-in-billionaire-mukesh-ambanis-jio-juggernaut%2F%3Fsh%3D1e725d971990%5C%22%3EReliance%20Jio%20raised%20for%2033%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20company.%20These%20investments%20did%20not%20really%20result%20in%20an%20increase%20in%20fresh%20employment.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20acquisition%20of%20technology%20shares%20formed%20a%20substantial%20chunk%20of%20FDI%20inflows%20into%20India%20in%20recent%20years.%20This%20has%20dried%20up%20in%202023%2C%20and%20is%20clearly%20showing%20up%20in%20the%2092%25%20decline%20in%20cross-border%20mergers%20and%20acquisitions%2C%E2%80%9D%20as%20pointed%20out%20by%20a%20Grant%20Thornton%20analyst%20on%20CNBC%20TV18.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20last%20two%20years%20of%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20tenure%20may%20bring%20in%20the%20lowest%20FDI.%20The%20government%20is%20trying%20its%20best%20to%20build%20a%20narrative%20projecting%20India%20is%20the%20fastest-growing%20economy%20post-COVID-19.%20But%20the%20reality%20is%20that%20there%20is%20a%20general%20decline%20in%20FDI%20flows%20globally%2C%20and%20India%20is%20not%20bucking%20the%20trend%2C%E2%80%9D%3Cem%3E%20The%20Wire%20%3C%2Fem%3Ereported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOne%20Rank%20One%20Pension%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20Rank%20One%20Pension%20(OROP)%20was%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20calling%20card%20where%20the%20defence%20forces%20were%20concerned.%20OROP%20was%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fmagazine%2Fstory%2Fshadow-of-a-promise%2F294133%5C%22%3Epromise%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Modi%20said%20he%20would%20implement%20if%20voted%20to%20power%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%202015%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%20was%20less%20ebullient.%20At%20a%20%3Cem%3EMann%20ki%20Baat%3C%2Fem%3E%20radio%20address%20in%202015%2C%20Modi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moneylife.in%2Farticle%2Fone-rank-one-pension-matter-of-faith-for-me-modi%2F42035.html%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CFor%2040%20years%2C%20this%20(OROP)%20question%20has%20been%20persisting.%20Nothing%20has%20happened%20so%20far%E2%80%A6It%20is%20not%20as%20simple%20as%20we%20thought%2C%20it%20is%20complicated%2C%20and%2040%20years%20have%20added%20to%20the%20complications.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20a%20June%202019%20parliament%20question%20on%20the%20status%20of%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20scheme%2C%20the%20government%20said%20orders%20had%20been%20issued%20in%20November%202015%20for%20implementing%20the%20scheme%20with%20effect%20from%20July%202014.%20Payment%20of%20arrears%20to%20the%20tune%20of%20Rs%2010%2C795.40%20crore%20has%20been%20made%20from%20Defence%20Pension%20Budget%20Estimates%2C%20the%20response%20said.%20In%20the%20same%20breath%2C%20it%20also%20admitted%20that%20there%20is%20no%20separate%20allocation%2Fbudgeting%20towards%20OROP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20nine%20years%2C%20the%20government%20has%20realised%20that%20OROP%20is%20easier%20said%20than%20done%2C%20with%20ex-servicemen%20hauling%20the%20government%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20In%20March%20this%20year%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Forop-one-time-payment-fiscal-implications%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20it%20is%20unable%20to%20pay%20OROP%20arrears%20in%20a%20single%20instalment%20but%20will%20do%20so%20in%20three%20equal%20instalments%20by%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20asked%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20comply%20with%20its%202022%20judgment%20on%20the%20payment%20of%20OROP%20arrears%20to%20ex-service%20personnel%20and%20asked%20it%20to%20pay%20dues%20for%202019-2022%20worth%20Rs%2028%2C000%20crore%20by%20February%2028%2C%202024.%20In%20December%202022%2C%20the%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fcabinet-revises-orop-25-12-lakh-army-pensioners-to-benefit-arrear-from-2019-101671808313251.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Union%2520Cabinet%2520on%2520Friday%2C25.13%2520lakh%2520Armed%2520Forces%2520pensioners.%5C%22%3Erevised%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20pension%20scheme%20to%20benefit%2025%20lakh%20pensioners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDigital%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDemonetisation%20was%20hailed%20as%20a%20push%20to%20digitalise%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Fevery-village-will-get-optical-fiber-internet-in-1-000-days-pm-modi-in-independence-day-speech-1711415-2020-08-15%5C%22%3E2020%20Independence%20Day%20speech%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%20promised%20to%20connect%20%E2%80%98every%20village%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%99%20with%20optical%20fibre%20within%20the%20coming%201%2C000%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%201.5%20lakh%20gram%20panchayats%20in%20the%20country%20have%20been%20connected%20with%20optical%20fibre%20cables.%20Before%202014%2C%20only%205%20dozen%20panchayats%20in%20the%20country%20were%20connected%20with%20optical%20fibre.%20Now%2C%20our%20aim%20is%20to%20connect%20every%20village%20with%20high-speed%20internet.%20This%20goal%20will%20be%20met%20in%20the%20coming%20thousand%20days%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Optical%20Fibre%20Network%20%E2%80%93%20later%20renamed%20as%20Bharat%20Net%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.factchecker.in%2Fpms-failed-promise-of-broadband-to-every-indian-village%2F%5C%22%3Ewas%20launched%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202011%2C%20to%20connect%202.5%20lakh%20gram%20panchayats.%20However%2C%20according%20to%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20the%20scheme%20took%20off%20only%20after%20his%20government%20came%20to%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%202022%20this%20picture%20had%20improved%20further%20as%20per%20a%20response%20to%20a%20parliament%20question.%20%E2%80%9CAs%20on%2030.09.2022%2C%20a%20total%20of%2035.5%20Lakh%20Route%20Kms%20Optical%20Fibre%20Cable%20(OFC)%20has%20already%20been%20laid%20in%20the%20country%2C%20which%20will%20facilitate%20the%20increasing%20demand%20for%20better%20bandwidth%2C%20resilient%20and%20high%20volume%20connectivity%2C%E2%80%9D%20Union%20minister%20of%20state%20for%20communications%20Devusinh%20Chauhan%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpqars.nic.in%2Fannex%2F258%2FAU1983.pdf%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20written%20reply%20to%20a%20question%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20in%20December%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2F05235140%2Finternet-map.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2F05235140%2Finternet-map.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2F05235140%2Finternet-map-300x134.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2F05235140%2Finternet-map-1024x458.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-446480%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22537%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMap%20depicting%20size%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20internet.%20Photo%3A%20Indi%20Samarajiva%2FFlickr%20CC-BY-2.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20closer%20look%20at%20the%20project%20throws%20up%20the%20following%20facts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20IAMAI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Ftech%2Ftechnology%2F52-of-indian-population-had-internet-access-in-2022-says-report%2Farticleshow%2F99964704.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%202022%20says%20India%20has%2052%25%20active%20internet%20users%20with%20rural%20India%20driving%20growth.%20But%20urban%20growth%20was%206%25%20in%202022%20and%20rural%20India%20witnessed%20only%20a%2014%25%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20deadline%20which%20had%20quietly%20been%20shifted%20from%201%2C000%20days%20in%202018%20to%202025.%20Even%20this%20looks%20difficult%20to%20implement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CInvolvement%20of%20multiple%20agencies%2C%20slow%20progress%20by%20implementing%20agencies%2C%20delay%20in%20right%20of%20way%20clearances%20from%20government%20instrumentalities%20regulating%20forest%20land%2C%20railway%20lines%2C%20defence%20areas%2C%20highways%2C%20oil%20and%20gas%20pipelines%2C%20or%20any%20other%20agencies%20or%20departments%20are%20some%20of%20the%20reasons%20for%20delay%20in%20implementation%20of%20the%20BharatNet%20project%2C%E2%80%9D%20minister%20of%20state%20for%20communications%20Devusinh%20Chauhah%20had%20said%20in%20Parliament%20in%20December%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20PPP%20model%20the%20government%20was%20banking%20on%20too%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20found%20any%20takers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGlobal%20bids%20were%20invited%20on%2020%20July%202021%20for%20implementation%20of%20BharatNet%20under%20%C2%A0PPP%20model.%20However%20no%20response%20was%20received%20from%20any%20of%20the%20prospective%20bidders.%20A%20revised%20strategy%20for%20BharatNet%20is%20accordingly%20being%20formulated%2C%E2%80%9D%20Chauhan%20had%20said%20in%20July%20last%20year%20in%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20reason%20is%20underspending%20of%20funds%20allocated%20for%20the%20project.%20%E2%80%9CA%20significant%20cut%20in%20spending%20from%20the%20Universal%20Service%20Obligation%20Fund%20(USOF)%20in%20FY23%20against%20the%20Budget%20targets%20indicates%20that%20for%20the%20sixth%20continuous%20year%2C%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20spending%20to%20provide%20connectivity%20to%20rural%20and%20remote%20areas%20to%20bridge%20the%20digital%20divide%20has%20slowed%20down%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20a%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.financialexpress.com%2Feconomy%2Fslow-govt-spending-tohit-rural-connectivity%2F2971676%2F%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESwachh%20Bharat%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20Independence%20Day%20speech%20in%202015%2C%20Modi%20said%20that%20his%20government%20would%20solve%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20sanitation%20problems%20by%202019.%20In%20his%20next%20Independence%20Day%20speech%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Ffreedom-must-lead-to-good-governance-pm-on-independence-day%2Farticleshow%2F53704603.cms%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20two%20crore%20toilets%20had%20been%20built%20and%2070%2C000%20villages%20made%20open%20defecation%20free%20(ODF).%20In%20his%202019%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesstoday.in%2Flatest%2Feconomy-politics%2Fstory%2Findependence-day-pm-modi-address-nation-full-text-speech-15-august-red-fort-222154-2019-08-15%5C%22%3Espeech%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Modi%20said%20that%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnext%20few%20weeks%E2%80%9D%2C%20India%20will%20declare%20itself%20ODF.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20October%202%2C%202019%20rural%20India%20declared%20itself%20ODF.%20Coincidentally%2C%202019%20was%20also%20the%20150th%20birth%20anniversary%20of%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%2C%20the%20self-effacing%20champion%20of%20cleanliness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20changed%20the%20narrative.%20People%20used%20to%20hesitate%20in%20talking%20about%20toilets.%20Now%2C%20it%20is%20a%20part%20of%20the%20conversation%20from%20Bollywood%20to%20the%20field%20of%20sports%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmodi-declares-rural-india-open-defecation-free-questions-remain%5C%22%3EModi%20said%20then%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%2060%20months%2C%20we%20have%20provided%20toilets%20to%20over%2060%20crore%20people%20by%20constructing%20over%2011%20crore%20toilets.%20The%20world%20is%20amazed%20on%20hearing%20this%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20As%20per%20Census%202011%2C%2070%25%20of%20rural%20households%20did%20not%20own%20a%20toilet.%20Now%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Swachh%20Bharat%20Mission%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fswachhbharatmission.gov.in%2Fsbmcms%2Findex.htm%5C%22%3Edatabase%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20100%25%20of%20households%20in%20India%20have%20access%20to%20toilets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20did%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fa-failed-attempt-to-create-an-equally-sanitary-india%5C%22%3E24-part%20series%3C%2Fa%3E%20covering%20the%20sanitation%20crisis%20in%20each%20Indian%20state.%20Some%20of%20the%20preliminary%20findings%20said%20the%20Swachh%20Bharat%20Mission%20websites%20have%20been%20showcasing%20over%2030%25%20manufactured%20data%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewith%20over%2012%20lakh%20toilets%20%E2%80%98constructed%E2%80%99%20between%202014%20and%202020%20that%20do%20not%20exist%2C%20and%20beneficiaries%20who%20have%20no%20knowledge%20of%20the%20toilets%20apparently%20built%20in%20their%20houses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fa-failed-attempt-to-create-an-equally-sanitary-india%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20data%20on%20several%20districts%E2%80%99%20ODF%20status%20was%20also%20found%20to%20be%20manufactured%2C%20with%20over%2020%20million%20people%20in%20rural%20areas%20still%20defecating%20in%20the%20open.%20Bihar%2C%20Odisha%20and%20Tripura%20are%20the%20worst%20performers%20in%20actual%20ODF%20estimates%2C%20despite%20declarations%20to%20the%20contrary%20on%20their%20government%20websites.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20added%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CMany%20surveys%20since%202017%20have%20found%20that%20of%20the%20households%20which%20have%20toilet%20access%2C%20over%2030%25%20are%20never%20used.%20In%202021%2C%20the%20survey%20found%2C%20more%20than%2045%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20population%20still%20defecates%20in%20the%20open.%20The%20reason%20for%20this%20is%20the%20non-maintenance%20of%20built%20toilets%20in%20combination%20with%20usage%20of%20substandard%20materials%20for%20construction.%20False%20claims%20by%20the%20government%20like%20%E2%80%985.5%20lakh%20sanitation%20workers%20have%20been%20linked%20to%20social%20welfare%20schemes%E2%80%99%20further%20worsens%20their%20conditions.%20With%20poor%20implementation%20in%20rural%20areas%2C%20over%20three%20lakh%20sanitation%20workers%20and%20waste%20workers%20are%20facing%20risks%20%E2%80%93%20and%20not%20benefits%20%E2%80%93%20from%20toilets%20built%20under%20this%20Mission%2C%20since%20they%20live%20on%20the%20peripheries%20of%20%E2%80%98dumping%20sites%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692103022000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15175959%2Fmodi-speeches.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpm-modi-big-ticket-announcements-red-fort-square-up%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Over%20the%20years%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20has%20made%20several%20promises%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0from%20doubling%20farmers'%20incomes%20to%20improving%20internet%20access%20and%20Swachh%20Bharat.%20The%20Wire%20looks%20how%20the%20government%20has%20fared%20in%20these%20aspects.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A35%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpm-modi-big-ticket-announcements-red-fort-square-up%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Holidaymakers%20flee%20as%20huge%20wildfire%20in%20France%20forces%20evacuations%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692100200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.